body:
@bnoordhuis that's really good news. I'm sure you'll manage but if you have questions regarding cmake let me know, I've got quite some experience with more complex setups.  

@saghul, @bnoordhuis some other open source projects seem to be somewhat resilient to support cmake too (although most projects are switching to cmake). Biggest argument of not using cmake is "we don't want to add another build system", but truth is, that once you've setup cmake it won't take much time to keep it updated; especially compared to the amount of actual coding you do. 
I also think that it would be perfectly valid to add CMake but communicate that the gyp solution is still the official way to go and cmake is only there for people who want to use cmake. Because as long as there is no cmake file in the libuv repository nobody can actually help maintaining it.
